			<ns0:name>dsch...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/104270846665912603141/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">After the switch to 32-bit host binaries for llvm and binutils the bmm and dbms tests from the LLVM test suite fail in the run stage. It seems to be that it's only when the support files in the toolchain package are compiled with the 32 bit toolchain that this happens.

i.e. it fails if you build the toolchain with 'HOST_ARCH=x86-32 build.sh everything; build.sh build-host; build.sh driver' but not if you do 'build.sh everything; HOST_ARCH=x86-32 build.sh build-host; HOST_ARCH=x86-32 build.sh driver'
If you do the latter it doesn't matter whether you use the 32-bit or 64-bit tools to translate and link nexes.</ns0:content><ns0:updated>2012-10-01T19:41:33.000Z</ns0:updated><ns0:published>2012-09-17T17:22:15.000Z</ns0:published><ns2:status>Fixed</ns2:status><ns2:cc>
